            <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">
              <Heading>Abstract</Heading>
              <Para>In this paper we extend our previous results concerning Jackson integral solutions of the boundary quantum Knizhnik–Zamolodchikov (qKZ) equations with diagonal <Emphasis Type="Italic">K</Emphasis>-operators to higher spin representations of quantum affine <InlineEquation ID="IEq1">
                  <InlineMediaObject>
                    <ImageObject Color="BlackWhite" FileRef="23_2014_395_Article_IEq1.gif" Format="GIF" Rendition="HTML" Type="Linedraw"/>
                  </InlineMediaObject>
                  <EquationSource Format="TEX"><![CDATA[$${\mathfrak{sl}_2}$$]]></EquationSource>
                  <EquationSource Format="MATHML">
                    <math xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                      <msub>
                        <mi mathvariant="fraktur">sl</mi>
                        <mn>2</mn>
                      </msub>
                    </math>
                  </EquationSource>
                </InlineEquation>. First we give a systematic exposition of known results on <Emphasis Type="Italic">R</Emphasis>-operators acting in the tensor product of evaluation representations in Verma modules over quantum <InlineEquation ID="IEq2">
                  <InlineMediaObject>
                    <ImageObject Color="BlackWhite" FileRef="23_2014_395_Article_IEq2.gif" Format="GIF" Rendition="HTML" Type="Linedraw"/>
                  </InlineMediaObject>
                  <EquationSource Format="TEX"><![CDATA[$${\mathfrak{sl}_2}$$]]></EquationSource>
                  <EquationSource Format="MATHML">
                    <math xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
                      <msub>
                        <mi mathvariant="fraktur">sl</mi>
                        <mn>2</mn>
                      </msub>
                    </math>
                  </EquationSource>
                </InlineEquation>. We develop the corresponding fusion of <Emphasis Type="Italic">K</Emphasis>-operators, which we use to construct diagonal <Emphasis Type="Italic">K</Emphasis>-operators in these representations. We construct Jackson integral solutions of the associated boundary qKZ equations and explain how in the finite-dimensional case they can be obtained from our previous results by the fusion procedure.</Para>
            </Abstract>
